title: Parser Error
body:
### Is there an existing issue for this?

- [X] I have searched the existing issues

### Bug description

I am getting an issue with DeepLabCut when using the site packages. I'm not sure if there's an issue with the yaml file or what the parsing error means. This is my first time using deeplabcut so any help would be appreciated! 

This is the error it is giving me: 
  "File "C:\Users\Anaconda3\envs\DEEPLABCUT\lib\site-packages\deeplabcut\pose_estimation_tensorflow\predict_videos.py", line 481, in analyze_videos
    cfg = auxiliaryfunctions.read_config(config)
  File "C:\Users\Anaconda3\envs\DEEPLABCUT\lib\site-packages\deeplabcut\utils\auxiliaryfunctions.py", line 179, in read_config
    cfg = ruamelFile.load(f)
  File "C:\Users\Anaconda3\envs\DEEPLABCUT\lib\site-packages\ruamel\yaml\main.py", line 434, in load
    return constructor.get_single_data()
  File "C:\Users\Anaconda3\envs\DEEPLABCUT\lib\site-packages\ruamel\yaml\constructor.py", line 119, in get_single_data
    node = self.composer.get_single_node()
  File "C:\Users\Anaconda3\envs\DEEPLABCUT\lib\site-packages\ruamel\yaml\composer.py", line 76, in get_single_node
    document = self.compose_document()
  File "C:\Users\Anaconda3\envs\DEEPLABCUT\lib\site-packages\ruamel\yaml\composer.py", line 99, in compose_document
    node = self.compose_node(None, None)
  File "C:\Users\Anaconda3\envs\DEEPLABCUT\lib\site-packages\ruamel\yaml\composer.py", line 143, in compose_node
    node = self.compose_mapping_node(anchor)
  File "C:\Users\Anaconda3\envs\DEEPLABCUT\lib\site-packages\ruamel\yaml\composer.py", line 216, in compose_mapping_node
    while not self.parser.check_event(MappingEndEvent):
  File "C:\Users\Anaconda3\envs\DEEPLABCUT\lib\site-packages\ruamel\yaml\parser.py", line 146, in check_event
    self.current_event = self.state()
  File "C:\Users\Anaconda3\envs\DEEPLABCUT\lib\site-packages\ruamel\yaml\parser.py", line 612, in parse_block_mapping_key
    raise ParserError(
ruamel.yaml.parser.ParserError: while parsing a block mapping"
